President Obama has announced a Presidential Delegation to attend the Closing Ceremony of the 2016 Olympic Summer Games in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. The delegation, led by Gina McCarthy, the Administrator of the United States Environmental Protection Agency, will attend athletic events, meet with U.S. athletes, and attend the Closing Ceremony. Other members of the delegation include Liliana Ayalde, U.S. Ambassador to Brazil, Eric Fanning, Secretary of the Army, Bess Evans, Senior Associate Director and Senior Policy Advisor, Lauren Kelly, Deputy Director and Deputy Social Secretary, Jason Collins, Retired NBA Player and Member of the President's Council on Fitness, Sports, and Nutrition, and Jackie Joyner-Kersee, three-time Olympic gold medalist and Founder of the Jackie Joyner-Kersee Foundation.